Since language assembly is a low level machine language, it is part of the primitive types of the c++
language . Primitive types are nothing more than the smallest data type that a language can have

Arrays are the first outlook to create abstract data types

Definition :: an array is a contiguous group of homogenous elements

Contiguous meaning that they sit next to each other in memory one right after another in sequential
fashion

Homogenous meaning that they are always The same type
